<br>
On the main topic, we have nobody to blame but ourselves.  All the bellyaching about how worthless our class is in PvE has raised a generation of DA players that believes it.<br>
<br>
I don't have that tough a time getting groups, but I do have to pester because I won't ever get invited unless I ask.  However, just about every time I group, there is at least one person who says, &quot;Gee, SB's actually do pretty well?&quot; when we break up.<br>
<br>
We contribute to the group damage just as well as anyone, and don't drain any additional resources if we're not being brash.  And heck, the other night our warrior and thane logged for the night, and I played main tank on reds in a group of 4.  We did just fine with only subtly altered tactics from the heavy tank scenario.<br>
<br>
If you're sure you know what you're doing - look for small groups in the areas you want to level - be a pest (although a friendly pest) and let them know you have something to offer.  Eventually you'll find people who will accept you in - and then do a hell of a good job, make some friends, and add them to your friends list to keep in touch with.  It doesn't take that long before you have a pretty good network you can hook up with for some serious levelling, if you've proven your worth. <p>Drolk - L43 Kobold Shadowblade (Tristan)<BR><i>In the shadow of the valley of death, I walk alone.</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ularlanalavode.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Larlana Lavode</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 2:29:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2804.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: detaunt</span><hr size=1> Reputation will help quite a bit.  Sometimes it is a matter of us forming groups for whatever region/dungeon is desired.  Many times if I do not have family members who are awake, or they are way too high to join, or just too deep into a dungeon to join, I will send a message out to my alliance that I am forming up a group, be it Spindy, the werewolf dungeon, battlegrounds (frontiers), or what have you.  And while the responses do not flood in, I will get some responses.  From there, it is a matter of networking.<br>
<br>
As was stated earlier, knowing how to play your profession helps quite a bit.  And yes, we are probably the least desired class out there as far as PvE is concerned.  But if you can learn how to take the initiative, form good, desirable groups, and have some skill in giving instructions (that does not mean telling someone how to play their class), then your reputation alone will make it easier to find groups.  If that doesn't help, then a nice little guilt trip from time to time helps as your alliance mates realize on their RvR trip that they have no decent level rogues in their midst to be able to help protect against enemy assassins.<br>
<br>
<br>
Larlana Lavode<br>
Mistress of Assassins<br>
Einherjar<br>
Midgard/Percival <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufgnn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fgnn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 6:42:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2804.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: detaunt</span><hr size=1> I also have no problems in groups. I'll first wait for the tank to get it first hit in (Or if he misses wait for the second), then perf, hoarfrost(detaunt), and pincer the rest of the fight. Pincer is great, becuase a: Higher chance to hit, b: half the endurance use. The couple damage less damage you do per hit is made up for when you hit them every time, and have enough endurance for 2 fights.<br>
<br>
If you have a good tank at least your level then it is real easy to not get hit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umeepoelfkiller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>meepo elfkiller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 8:25:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2804.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pincer vs Assault Ice Storm</span><hr size=1> My question is I see alot of people advocating the use of pimcer, which is cool. What I'm wondering is how does pincer stack against the Assault Ice Storm combo that you get from sword skill. I am a crit blade and thus at lvl 37 have a 34 crit 33 sword 28 stealth. The assault/ice storm is what I use since it can be used from any position (which helps when the mob changes targets frequently)Since I use a 2 hander and assault doesn't use much end. I usually can go 2 fights or so before needing to sit (I almost never get aggro with this combo btw, unless I taunt to pull aggro form the healer) Also if anyone with a 34 sword could tell me if the 34 use anytime sword style is worth it ? Just curious as to how the assault/ice storm and lvl 34 use anytime sword styles stack up against pincer in group PvE. Well anyone with any thoughts or opinions is encouraged to post, just tryin to play the most group friendly blade I can <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
